The symmetric difference A Δ B consists of elements that are in A or B but NOT in both (i.e. elements in exactly one of the sets):
A Δ B = (A ∪ B) − (A ∩ B) = (A − B) ∪ (B − A)

A ∩ B (elements in both): {−3, 0, 3}

A − B (in A but not B): {−5, −1, 1, 2}
B − A (in B but not A): {−4, 5, 8}

A Δ B = {−5, −4, −1, 1, 2, 5, 8}
